ts, or interact with our website/widget. It applies to visitors, customers, and authorized users of business accounts.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>2) Roles</strong></h2><ul><li value="1"><strong>Data Controller:</strong>[Company Legal Name] for all customer data processed via our platform.</li><li value="2"><strong>Processors/Sub-processors:</strong>service providers acting on our instructions (see Section 9 and Appendix A).</li><li value="3"><strong>Independent Controllers:</strong>some partners (e.g., payment institutions) may act as independent controllers for their own compliance obligations.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>3) Categories of Data We Process</strong></h2><ul><li value="1"><strong>Account &amp; profile:</strong>name, email, phone, password hash, language, country.</li><li value="2"><strong>KYC/KYB data:</strong>identity details (e.g., name, DOB, nationality), document metadata (ID/Passport details, issuer, expiry), proof of address metadata, company registration data, UBO/directors, PEP information.</li><li value="3"><strong>Biometric data (with explicit consent):</strong>selfie/liveness checks used solely for identity verification.</li><li value="4"><strong>Transaction data:</strong>payment method, amounts, currency, assets purchased, wallet addresses (sender/beneficiary), order IDs, timestamps.</li><li value="5"><strong>Compliance data:</strong>sanctions/PEP/adverse media screening results, risk scores, flags and review notes.</li><li value="6"><strong>Technical data:</strong>device/OS/browser, IP, cookies/SDK identifiers, logs, fraud signals.</li><li value="7"><strong>Support &amp; feedback:</strong>tickets, messages, recordings (if applicable).</li></ul><blockquote>We do<strong>not</strong>custody your crypto. For self-custody payouts, we may verify wallet ownership where required by law.</blockquote><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>4) Purposes &amp; Legal Bases</strong></h2><p>We process data for:</p><ol><li value="1"><strong>Account creation &amp; service delivery</strong>(Art. 6(1)(b) GDPR).</li><li value="2"><strong>AML/KYC/CTF compliance, Travel Rule, record-keeping</strong>(Art. 6(1)(c) GDPR; legal obligation under AMLD and EU 2023/1113).</li><li value="3"><strong>Risk management &amp; fraud prevention</strong>(Art. 6(1)(f) legitimate interests; necessary security measures).</li><li value="4"><strong>Payments &amp; billing</strong>(Art. 6(1)(b)).</li><li value="5"><strong>Customer support &amp; communications</strong>(Art. 6(1)(b)/(f)).</li><li value="6"><strong>Analytics &amp; performance</strong>(Art. 6(1)(a) consent for non-essential cookies; or 6(1)(f) where permitted).</li><li value="7"><strong>Marketing communications</strong>(Art. 6(1)(a) consent; opt-out anytime).</li></ol><p><strong>Biometrics:</strong>We process<strong>selfie/liveness</strong>data<strong>only with your explicit consent</strong>(Art. 9(2)(a) GDPR) and solely for identity verification.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>5) Travel Rule &amp; Wallet Ownership</strong></h2><p>For crypto transfers, we may be legally required to transmit originator/beneficiary information to authorized providers/counterparties (EU Transfers of Funds Regulation). For self-hosted wallets and transactions exceeding regulatory thresholds, we may request proof of wallet ownership (e.g., signed message, micro-transfer).</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>6) How We Collect Data</strong></h2><ul><li value="1">Directly from you (forms, KYC flow, support).</li><li value="2">Automatically via cookies/SDKs and security tooling.</li><li value="3">From third parties: identity verification providers, payment processors, sanctions/PEP databases, and, for KYB, public registers.</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>7) Retention</strong></h2><p>We keep data<strong>only as long as necessary</strong>and in line with legal duties:</p><ul><li value="1"><strong>KYC/KYB &amp; transaction records:</strong><strong> 5 years</strong>after the end of the business relationship or per local AML law.</li><li value="2"><strong>Compliance logs &amp; risk assessments:</strong><strong> 5 years</strong>.</li><li value="3"><strong>Account data:</strong>as long as the account is active; then as required for legal claims/defence.</li><li value="4"><strong>Marketing:</strong>until you withdraw consent or after [24] months of inactivity.</li><li value="5"><strong>Cookies/logs:</strong>per Cookie Policy (typ. 1224 months for analytics; session for strictly necessary).</li></ul><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>8) Security</strong></h2><p>We implement organizational and technical measures including encryption in transit/at rest (where applicable), access controls (least privilege, MFA), network segmentation, monitoring, incident response, and vendor due diligence. If a personal data breach occurs, we will notify the supervisory authority and affected individuals when required by law.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>9) Sharing &amp; Recipients</strong></h2><p>We share data strictly on a need-to-know basis with:</p><ul><li value="1"><strong>Identity/KYC provider(s):</strong>e.g.,<strong>KYCAID</strong>(document capture, liveness, screening).</li><li value="2"><strong>Payment processor(s)/acquirers:</strong>e.g.,<strong>Rapyd</strong>(card acquiring, payouts).</li><li value="3"><strong>Blockchain analytics / screening:</strong>[Vendor, if used].</li><li value="4"><strong>Hosting &amp; infrastructure:</strong>[Cloud/VPS provider, region], [CDN/DNS], [Email/SMS provider].</li><li value="5"><strong>Fraud &amp; security tools:</strong>[Tools].</li><li value="6"><strong>Professional advisors &amp; auditors:</strong>where necessary.</li><li value="7"><strong>Authorities:</strong>upon lawful request or to comply with AML/CTF, sanctions, court orders.</li></ul><p>An up-to-date list of processors is maintained in<strong>Appendix A</strong>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>10) International Transfers</strong></h2><p>Where data is transferred outside the EEA/UK, we rely on<strong>adequacy decisions</strong>or<strong>Standard Contractual Clauses (SCCs)</strong>and apply supplementary measures (encryption, minimization). You can request a copy of the relevant safeguards.</p><h2><strong>11) Your Rights (GDPR)</strong></h2><p>You have the right to request:</p><ul><li value="1">access, rectification, erasure, restriction, data portability, and to object to processing based on legitimate interests.</li><li value="2">to withdraw consent at any time (e.g., biometrics or marketing).</li><li value="3">to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.</li></ul><p><strong>Supervisory authority (Poland):</strong>President of the Personal Data Protection Office (UODO), [uodo.gov.pl], or your local EU authority.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>12) Children</strong></h2><p>Our services are not directed to individuals under<strong>18</strong>. We do not knowingly collect data from minors.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>13) Cookies &amp; Similar Technologies</strong></h2><p>We use strictly necessary cookies for security and operation; optional analytics/marketing cookies are used<strong>only with your consent</strong>via our Cookie Banner/Consent Management Platform. Details, categories, and lifetimes are described in our<strong>Cookie Policy</strong>.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>14) Automated Decision-Making</strong></h2><p>We do<strong>not</strong>make decisions producing legal or similarly significant effects<strong>solely</strong>by automated means. Risk scoring and screening support manual reviews by our compliance team.</p><p>&nbsp;</p><h2><strong>15) Contact</strong></h2><p>For privacy requests or questions, contact:<strong>[privacy@your-domain.tld]</strong></p><p>If appointed, our DPO:<strong>[Name, email]</strong>.</p><h2><strong>16) Changes</strong></h2><p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post changes on this page and update the Last updated date. Material changes may be notified by email or in-product messages.</p><h2><strong>Appendix A  Processors &amp; Key Partners (example placeholders)</strong></h2><p><strong>Identity verification (KYC/KYB &amp; biometrics)</strong></p><ul><li value="1">KYCAID Limited  document capture, liveness, screening. SCCs/EEA hosting: [Yes/No]. DPA in place.</li></ul><p><strong>Payments &amp; payouts</strong></p><ul><li value="1">Rapyd Europe / [entity]  card acquiring, payments. Independent controller for some processing activities.</li></ul><p><strong>Hosting &amp; infrastructure</strong></p><ul><li value="1">[Cloud Provider] (EU region)  application hosting, storage.</li><li value="2">[Email/SMS provider]  transactional communications.</li><li value="3">[CDN/DNS]  content delivery/security.</li></ul><p><strong>Analytics / Security (optional)</strong></p><ul><li value="1">[Analytics Tool]  aggregated usage analytics (consent-based).</li><li value="2">[Fraud/Security Tool]  threat detection, bot protection.</li></ul><blockquote>We maintain a current list of processors and sub-processors at: [link to Sub-processors page].</blockquote>	1) Scope\nThis Privacy Policy explains how we process personal data when you use our services, create an account, complete KYC/KYB verification, make payments, or interact with our website/widget. It applies to visitors, customers, and authorized users of business accounts.\n\n2) Roles\nData Controller:[Company Legal Name] for all customer data processed via our platform.\nProcessors/Sub-processors:service providers acting on our instructions (see Section 9 and Appendix A).\nIndependent Controllers:some partners (e.g., payment institutions) may act as independent controllers for their own compliance obligations.\n\n3) Categories of Data We Process\nAccount & profile:name, email, phone, password hash, language, country.\nKYC/KYB data:identity details (e.g., name, DOB, nationality), document metadata (ID/Passport details, issuer, expiry), proof of address metadata, company registration data, UBO/directors, PEP information.\nBiometric data (with explicit c