nsaction records: 5 yearsafter the end of the business relationship or per local AML law.\nCompliance logs & risk assessments: 5 years.\nAccount data:as long as the account is active; then as required for legal claims/defence.\nMarketing:until you withdraw consent or after [24] months of inactivity.\nCookies/logs:per Cookie Policy (typ. 1224 months for analytics; session for strictly necessary).\n\n8) Security\nWe implement organizational and technical measures including encryption in transit/at rest (where applicable), access controls (least privilege, MFA), network segmentation, monitoring, incident response, and vendor due diligence. If a personal data breach occurs, we will notify the supervisory authority and affected individuals when required by law.\n\n9) Sharing & Recipients\nWe share data strictly on a need-to-know basis with:\nIdentity/KYC provider(s):e.g.,KYCAID(document capture, liveness, screening).\nPayment processor(s)/acquirers:e.g.,Rapyd(card acquiring, payouts).\nBlockchain analytics / screening:[Vendor, if used].\nHosting & infrastructure:[Cloud/VPS provider, region], [CDN/DNS], [Email/SMS provider].\nFraud & security tools:[Tools].\nProfessional advisors & auditors:where necessary.\nAuthorities:upon lawful request or to comply with AML/CTF, sanctions, court orders.\nAn up-to-date list of processors is maintained inAppendix A.\n\n10) International Transfers\nWhere data is transferred outside the EEA/UK, we rely onadequacy decisionsorStandard Contractual Clauses (SCCs)and apply supplementary measures (encryption, minimization). You can request a copy of the relevant safeguards.\n11) Your Rights (GDPR)\nYou have the right to request:\naccess, rectification, erasure, restriction, data portability, and to object to processing based on legitimate interests.\nto withdraw consent at any time (e.g., biometrics or marketing).\nto lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.\nSupervisory authority (Poland):President of the Personal Data Protection Office (UODO), [uodo.gov.pl], or your local EU authority.\n\n12) Children\nOur services are not directed to individuals under18. We do not knowingly collect data from minors.\n\n13) Cookies & Similar Technologies\nWe use strictly necessary cookies for security and operation; optional analytics/marketing cookies are usedonly with your consentvia our Cookie Banner/Consent Management Platform. Details, categories, and lifetimes are described in ourCookie Policy.\n\n14) Automated Decision-Making\nWe donotmake decisions producing legal or similarly significant effectssolelyby automated means. Risk scoring and screening support manual reviews by our compliance team.\n\n15) Contact\nFor privacy requests or questions, contact:[privacy@your-domain.tld]\nIf appointed, our DPO:[Name, email].\n16) Changes\nWe may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will post changes on this page and update the Last updated date. Material changes may be notified by email or in-product messages.\nAppendix A  Processors & Key Partners (example placeholders)\nIdentity verification (KYC/KYB & biometrics)\nKYCAID Limited  document capture, liveness, screening. SCCs/EEA hosting: [Yes/No]. DPA in place.\nPayments & payouts\nRapyd Europe / [entity]  card acquiring, payments. Independent controller for some processing activities.\nHosting & infrastructure\n[Cloud Provider] (EU region)  application hosting, storage.\n[Email/SMS provider]  transactional communications.\n[CDN/DNS]  content delivery/security.\nAnalytics / Security (optional)\n[Analytics Tool]  aggregated usage analytics (consent-based).\n[Fraud/Security Tool]  threat detection, bot protection.\nWe maintain a current list of processors and sub-processors at: [link to Sub-processors page].	PUBLISHED	2025-10-29 00:47:59.073	cmh82azsv000034wh1r5hq5tv	1	\N	t	Privacy Policy	\N	\N	f	{ADMIN}	cmh82azsv000034wh1r5hq5tv	cmhf097vk0000dpe5nzfluxgd	2025-10-29 00:47:51.881	2025-11-10 18:26:31.51	[{"action": "created", "userId": "cmh82azsv000034wh1r5